We are going to use the **MNIST** dataset. The MNIST dataset is a large database of handwritten digits. It commonly used for training various image processing systems. MNIST is short for Modified National Institute of Standards and Technology database.

It has **60,000** small square **28×28 pixel grayscale images** of handwritten single digits between 0 and 9.
